<HEAD>British Spelunker's Body Found in Cave</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRENOBLE, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The body of a young British spelunker missing since August was found Sunday in a cave near <LOCATION> Grenoble </LOCATION>, officials said. <PERSON> Alex </PERSON> <PERSON> Pritcher </PERSON>, 17, disappeared Aug. 7 after he became separated from 20 other young cave explorers. All were from <LOCATION> Manchester </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>. His companions reported him missing after he failed to appear at a meeting point outside the cave. For more than a week, a team of 170 French rescue workers searched inside and around the outside of the cave without finding <PERSON> Pritcher </PERSON>. On Sunday, a team of first-aid workers training in cave rescues discovered him at the bottom of a shaft near a network of chasms known as the Shepherd's Pit, according to local police officials. The pit plunges to a depth of 3,765 feet. Authorities said <PERSON> Pritcher </PERSON> probably died after being struck on the head and shoulders by falling rocks.
