<HEAD>Research Shows Drug Restores IQs of Children With AIDS</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DANIEL Q. HANEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Science Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An AIDS drug can dramatically boost the intelligence of youngsters whose brains are damaged by the AIDS virus and even restores their ability to walk and talk, researchers said Sunday. Damage to the brain is one of the earliest and most devastating of the effects of the lethal virus in children. The research suggests that the drug AZT can reverse these symptoms and apparently bring virus-damaged brain cells back to health. AZT, also known as zidovudine or Retrovir, is the only medicine routinely used to suppress the AIDS virus, called HIV. In adults, it can slow the progression of AIDS but does not cure it. The latest research, directed by Dr. <PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Pizzo </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cancer </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION>, was presented at the Fourth International Conference on AIDS. <PERSON> Pizzo </PERSON>'s findings came unexpectedly during testing of a portable pump to administer the drug to children. He found that youngsters' IQ scores increased about 15 points, and many of the other severe brain symptoms of the virus also went away `` Everybody who looks at this data has to get excited,'' said Dr. <PERSON> Daniel </PERSON> <PERSON> Hoth </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Institute </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Allergy </ORGANIZATION> and Infectious Diseases. `` We are all nervous by small numbers -LRB- of patients studied -RRB-, but the data itself is very exciting.'' More than 7,000 people, most of them doctors and scientists, from 138 countries gathered in <LOCATION> Stockholm </LOCATION> for the opening Sunday of the fourzoZO - -LRB- 64 | x -RCB- zys, there were 25 deaths among patients who got AZT alone, compared with 11 among people who got AIDS damages the body's immune system, leaving victims s