<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The average price of gasoline at the pump was virtually unchanged in early June compared with three weeks ago, an oil industry analyst said Sunday. The Lundberg Survey of 12,000 gasoline stations determined the average price per gallon was 100.23 cents as of June 10, down slightly from the May 20 average of 100.26 cents, said <PERSON> Trilby </PERSON> <PERSON> Lundberg </PERSON>. The survey said prices per gallon at self-service pumps were: regular unleaded 91.22 cents, premium unleaded 106.01 cents, regular leaded 88.24 cents. At full-service pumps, the survey said prices were: regular unleaded 119.80 cents, premium unleaded 129.89 cents, regular leaded 115.54 cents.
