g </PERSON> as a potential buyer. The newspaper said <PERSON> Greenberg </PERSON>'s deposition indicates the transaction never took place because the parties could not agree on a price. On Friday, <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> said he was forming a new holding company to act as his sole vehicle for acquisitions, including a possible hostile takeover bid for <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION>. He said the holding company intended to raise up to $ 3.25 billion through an offering of stock and debt securities. The <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> group of companies also will contribute equity to the holding company, including its 36.1 million shares of <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> and its interests in <ORGANIZATION> Trans </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> World </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> ACF </ORGANIZATION>, a leasing company. <PERSON> Icahn </PERSON> stated that if his slate was elected but a majority of the <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> board refused to allow a shareholder vote on the offer, he would consider making a hostile bid for it through the new holding company at yet to be determined terms.
